Biography

AT WASHINGTON

2023: Played in four regular-season games (preserving his redshirt year), and in all three postseason games, for seven appearances total ... made his UW debut in the win at Michigan State, where he had a half of a tackle for loss ... two tackles in the win over California ... also played at Stanford and at USC, where he had one tackle ... saw action in the Pac-12 Championship Game vs. Oregon.

HIGH SCHOOL

Played cornerback, wide receiver and returner for the Mustangs ... named his region's Player of the Year by the Daily Republic (Fairfield, Calif.) as a senior in 2022 ... also named to the all-region first team on both sides of the ball ... named Monticello Empire League Co-Player of the Year in 2022 ... also first-team all-league at both WR and CB ... as a senior, caught 58 passes for 837 yards and six touchdowns, while also rushing for a TD ... named to CalHiSports.com's 2022 preseason All-Sac-Joaquin Section first team ... ranked the No. 45 cornerback in the country and No. 35 overall prospect in California by 247Sports ... rated the No. 80 prospect in California by ESPN ... ranked the No. 45 "athlete" and No. 59 prospect in California by Rivals ... only began playing football as a high-school sophomore ... also a standout on the basketball team ... named first-team all-league as a sophomore and junior in basketball ... played football for coach Myles King.
